column2: Heart failure patients' peripheral blood mononuclear cell gene expression profiles before mechanical circulatory support

This data represents whole transcriptome total RNA gene expression profiles of peripheral blood mononuclear cells collected from 29 advanced heart failure patients on the day before undergoing mechanical circulatory support surgery. Keywords = Advanced Heart Failure. Keywords =  Mechanical Circulatory Support. Keywords = Biological Age. Keywords = PBMC. Keywords = Immune Response. Keywords = Peripheral Blood. Keywords =Organ Function. Keywords = Recovery. Organism: Homo sapiens. Type: Expression profiling by array. Platforms: Illumina HiSeq 2500.
Heart failure patients' peripheral blood mononuclear cell gene expression profiles before mechanical circulatory support mechanical circulatory support surgery.
Expression profiling by high throughput sequencing

column2: Samples were collected on day one before mechanical circulatory support surgery. Eight ml of blood was drawn into a CPT tube (Becton Dickinson, Franklin Lakes, NJ). Peripheral Blood Mononuclear cells (PBMC) from each sample were purified within 2h of phlebotomy. The collected blood was mixed and centrifuged at room temperature (22⁰C) for 20min at 3000 RPM. The cell layer was collected, transferred to 15ml conical tubes and centrifuged for 20min at 1135 RPM at 4°C. The supernatant was aspirated and discharged. The cell pellet was resuspend in cold Phosphate Buffer Saline (Sigma-Aldrich, St. Louis, MO), transferred into an eppendorf tube and centrifuged for 20min at 5.6 RPM at 4°C. The supernatant was discharged. The pellet was resuspended in 0.5 ml RNA Protect Cell Reagent (Qiagen, Valencia, CA) and frozen at -80°C. The RNA was isolated from the PBMC using RNeasy Mini Kit (Qiagen, Valencia, CA).  The quality of the total RNA was assessed using NanoDrop® ND-8000 spectrophotometer (NanoDrop Technologies, Wilmington, DE) and Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies, Palo Alto, CA)  concentration above 50 ng/µl., purity - 260/280 ~ 2.0., integrity - RIN > 9.0 and average > 9.5.
